Someone may have lived a longer life (yes, even someone with 4+ comorbidities) if they hadn’t gotten covid. And covid causes other diseases! For example, someone’s death certificate may have had pneumonia on it with a secondary cause of covid
Now let’s compare that to covid. Hemophilia is a pre-existing condition (a comorbidity) while the car accident is covid.

If you did not experience the car accident, you would have been completely fine and would have lived longer. But because of the car accident, you died of exsanguination due to car accident (and it’s what will be put on your death certificate)
Let’s say you have hemophilia (slow blood clotting) and are in a car accident. You end up bleeding out and dying bc the paramedics arrived too late
Perhaps explaining things a bit different will help people understand

And we all have many! Lactose intolerance, needing glasses, asthma, anxiety, depression, anemia, are all examples of comorbidities
